C<SUB>2</SUB>O<SUB>4</SUB>: Extension of the Redox Chemistry Experiment =
(One or=20
more trials should be done by each person in the group for a total of at =
least 3=20
trials).</SPAN></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=3DMsoBodyTextIndent><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">All data =
should be=20
immediately exchanged between group members.&nbsp; The calculations and =
report=20
(interpretation) must be done individually. This approach is very =
similar to the=20
way questions are answered in industry and research where different =
individuals=20
do various aspects of projects and the results are combined to generate =
a=20
solution.</SPAN></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<H1><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 14pt">EXPERIMENTAL</SPAN></H1>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">EQUIPMENT AND=20
MATERIALS:</SPAN></B></P>
<P class=3DMsoBodyText=20
style=3D"VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; punctuation-wrap: simple">Two 100 mL =
beakers,=20
spatula, wash bottle, 25 mL graduated cylinder, watch glass, a small =
wide-mouth=20
amber bottle, filter paper, vacuum filtration setup (buchner funnel, =
rubber=20
adaptor, filter flask, pressure tubing, clamp, ring stand), oven, and a=20
dessicator.</P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">CHEMICALS:&nbsp; =

</SPAN></B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">The hazard code for each =
chemical is=20
listed inside parentheses.&nbsp; The order is (health/toxicity, =
flammability,=20
reactivity, and contact/corrosiveness).</SPAN></P>
<OL style=3D"MARGIN-TOP: 0in" type=3D1>
  <LI class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Potassium =
Oxalate,=20
  K<SUB>2</SUB>C<SUB>2</SUB>O<SUB>4 </SUB></SPAN><SPAN=20
  style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol">=B7</SPAN><SPAN=20
  style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> H<SUB>2</SUB>O (3013) - 24.0 grams per =
group</SPAN>=20
  <LI class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Iron (III) =
chloride (Ferric=20
  chloride), FeCl<SUB>3</SUB> (1012) - 16 mL of a 0.400 g/mL sol. per=20
  group</SPAN>=20
  <LI class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Acetone,=20
  CH<SUB>3</SUB>COCH<SUB>3 </SUB>(1321)</SPAN>=20
  <LI class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">RO water and =
ice.</SPAN>=20
  </LI></OL>
<H2><B><SPAN style=3D"TEXT-DECORATION: none">SAFETY CONCERNS: =
</SPAN></B></H2>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Risk Assessment: =
Low to=20
moderate due to acetone (flammable) and potassium oxalate (health=20
hazard).</SPAN></B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> All waste solutions =
except=20
acetone may be safely discarded down the drain.&nbsp; Acetone should be=20
collected in the bottle labeled =93Waste Acetone=94 in the hood.&nbsp; =
ACETONE IS A=20
FLAMMABLE SOLVENT; work with the acetone in the hood only.&nbsp; If a =
spill=20
occurs outside the hood, make sure all burners and hot plates in the =
area are=20
turned off.&nbsp; Sponge or mop up the spilled acetone or acetone =
mixture, and=20
use large quantities of water to rinse it down the drain. Potassium =
oxalate is=20
toxic, so avoid contact.</SPAN></P>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<H1>EXPERIMENTAL PROCEDURE:&nbsp; The Synthesis and Purification of an =
Iron Salt=20
</H1>
<H2 style=3D"MARGIN-TOP: 6pt">First Lab Period <SPAN=20
class=3DMsoCommentReference><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TEXT-DECORATION: none"><A></A><A =
language=3DJavaScript=20
class=3Dmsocomanchor id=3D_anchor_1=20
onmouseover=3D"msoCommentShow('_anchor_1','_com_1')"=20
onmouseout=3D"msoCommentHide('_com_1')"=20
